text: Klaas Boot (28 July 1898 - 12 May 1969) was a Dutch gymnast. He competed in seven events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1898 births Category:1969 deaths Category:Dutch male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the Netherlands Category:Gymnasts at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from North Holland
